%% PROPOSED: Integration & Verification Cross-Team Sequence
sequenceDiagram
    participant HW as HW Team
    participant SW as SW Team
    participant AUT as Autonomy
    participant AERO as Aero
    participant Q as Quality
    participant PE as Project Engineer
    participant SVP as SVP Engineering

    HW->>PE: Declare HW subsystem ready
    SW->>PE: Declare SW subsystem ready
    AUT->>PE: Declare autonomy subsystem ready
    AERO->>PE: Declare aero subsystem ready
    PE->>Q: Notify readiness package complete

    HW->>SW: Verify HW↔FW ICD
    SW->>AUT: Verify FW/Companion↔Autonomy interfaces
    AUT->>AERO: Verify autonomy↔aero assumptions
    Q->>HW: Witness interface verification evidence
    Q->>SW: Record interface verification results

    SW->>AUT: Run HITL test campaign
    AUT->>HW: Exercise behaviors on real hardware
    Q->>PE: Report HITL status

    HW->>SW: Assemble integrated aircraft
    SW->>AUT: Run system-level functional tests
    AUT->>AERO: Compare integrated behavior to expected performance
    Q->>PE: Record system integration and verification evidence

    HW->>Q: Submit as-built configuration records
    SW->>Q: Submit released software/autonomy versions
    AUT->>Q: Confirm behavior baseline used in verification
    AERO->>Q: Confirm supporting configuration assumptions
    Q->>PE: Complete configuration audit summary

    PE->>SVP: Present PRR package and recommendation
    SVP-->>PE: Approve production gate
    PE->>HW: Release design package to production
    PE->>SW: Release software package to production
    Q->>HW: Confirm controlled release records
